AGI - New show by Elon Musk.> Speaking at a Republican constituency in Wisconsin, the billionaire wore a cheese-shaped hat > and delivered two cheques > from one million dollars each to two people > who participated in the event and are lined up for the Conservative Judge candidate at the Wisconsin State Supreme Court.
The two winners, Nicholas Jacobs and Ekaterina Dressler, were awarded on stage by the South African billionaire. Musk reiterated the invitation to vote for the Republican candidate.&nbsp; "Have you noticed how much hatred comes from the left? They're threatening to kill the president, me. They are psychopaths," said Musk.&nbsp;
<div </div
The patron of tesla, who under the Trump administration is guiding the plan of mass dismissals of public employees, returned to talk about the death threats that concern him. "These protesters asked for the death of the president and me, and I don't know who else. At the cost of appearing outrageous, I say that asking for death, the assassination is not cool, no, asking is not cool." &nbsp;
